int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
This is the function which is invoked to receive an IPC message Messages can be received from either:- (a) Local: One thread is trying to control the TestFmk Profile (b) Remote: One core is trying to control the profile executing on the remote domain. Process all the messages

int32_t *  errCode 
)
static

Description
The function is used to process the response message. Response messages are received in lieu of a request. Successful responses will change the profile status and will ensure that the TestFmk instances are synchronized with each other
